The paper deals with channel estimation in millimeter-wave MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of a partially observable Markov decision process (POMDP) framework, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper focuses on the sparsity of mmWave MIMO channels, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM).
